  "prompt": "Which are the best books for bank exam?",
  "response": "Preparing for bank exams such as IBPS PO, SBI PO, RBI Grade B, and others requires a comprehensive strategy that includes understanding the exam pattern, practicing previous years' papers, and studying from the best resources. Here are some highly recommended books for various sections of bank exams:\n\n### Quantitative Aptitude:\n1. **\"Quantitative Aptitude for Competitive Examinations\" by R.S. Aggarwal** - This book covers a wide array of topics and includes numerous practice questions.\n2. **\"Fast Track Objective Arithmetic\" by Rajesh Verma** - Good for practicing shortcuts and quick methods.\n\n### Reasoning Ability:\n1. **\"A Modern Approach to Verbal & Non-Verbal Reasoning\" by R.S. Aggarwal** - Comprehensive coverage of reasoning topics with ample practice questions.\n2. **\"Analytical Reasoning\" by M.K. Pandey** - Focuses on conceptual clarity and offers detailed explanations.\n\n### English Language:\n1. **\"Objective General English\" by S.P. Bakshi** - A great resource for grammar, vocabulary, and comprehension.\n2. **\"Word Power Made Easy\" by Norman Lewis** - Excellent for building a strong vocabulary.\n\n### General Awareness:\n1. **\"Banking Awareness\" by Arihant Experts** - Specific to banking industry knowledge and current affairs.\n2. **\"Guide to Banking General Awareness\" by RPH Editorial Board** - Covers banking terminology, policies, and economic updates.\n\n### Computer Knowledge:\n1. **\"Computer Awareness\" by Arihant Experts** - Particularly useful for the computer knowledge section of bank exams.\n2. **\"Objective Computer Awareness\" by R. Pillai** - Comprehensive and detailed for banking exams.\n\n### Practice Papers and Previous Years' Papers:\n1. **\"Banking and Financial Awareness\" by Disha Experts** - Includes past papers and practice sets.\n2. **Previous Years\u2019 Question Papers by any reputed publisher (e.g., Kiran Prakashan, Arihant)** - Essential for understanding the exam pattern and practicing.\n\n### Additional Resources:\n1. **\"Manorama Yearbook\"** - Great for current affairs and general knowledge.\n2. **Monthly magazines like \"Pratiyogita Darpan\"** - Stay updated with current events and practice questions.\n\nThese books are well-regarded for their thorough content and practice questions, which are essential for clearing bank exams. Additionally, regular reading of newspapers like \"The Hindu\" or \"The Indian Express\" can be very beneficial for the General Awareness section.",
